The code statements that lead to the bug are:
```c
if (c->bpp <= 8 && c->palette_size) {
    avctx->pix_fmt = AV_PIX_FMT_PAL8;
}
```
Reason:
The absence of a check for `c->format` allows the code to incorrectly set the pixel format to `AV_PIX_FMT_PAL8` when `c->bpp` is less than or equal to 8 and `c->palette_size` is non-zero, without verifying if the format is `CHUNKY`. This can lead to an out-of-array access and potential crashes.

The code statements that fix the bug are:
```c
if (!encoding && c->palette_size && c->bpp <= 8 && c->format != CHUNKY) {
    avctx->pix_fmt = AV_PIX_FMT_PAL8;
}
```
Reason:
By adding the condition `&& c->format != CHUNKY`, the code now ensures that the pixel format is only set to `AV_PIX_FMT_PAL8` when the format is not `CHUNKY`, preventing the out-of-array access and ensuring valid memory access.

